{"lemma":"حِمَى","slug":"حِمَى","root":"ح.م.#","root_slug":"ح-م-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-م-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n9010","n9225","n9228"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%90%D9%85%D9%8E%D9%89"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَمَى (ḥamā) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"protecting, protection"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sheltering"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be protected from evil"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be extremely hot","examples":[{"text":"تَصْلَى نَارًا حَامِيَةً"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be angry","examples":[{"text":"حمِي المعلم على الطلاب المهملين"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9010","headword_ar":"حُمّى","root":"Hm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, &c.,) a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hum~","text_ar":"حُمّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, L, K,) imperfectly decl., because of the fem. alif [which terminates it], (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A fever; a disease by which the body becomes hot:"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHamiymu","text_ar":"الحَمِيمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": said to be so called because of the excessive heat; whence the trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHum~aY mino fayoHi jahan~ama","text_ar":"الحُمَّى مِنْ فَيْحِ جَهَنَّمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fever is from the exhalation of Hell"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or because of the sweat that occurs in it: or because it is of the signs of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHimaAm","text_ar":"الحِمَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. the decreed, or predestined, case of death]; for they say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHum~aY raAy^idu Almawoti","text_ar":"الحُمَّى رَايِدُ المَوْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fever is the messenger that precedes death"},{"kind":"text","text":"], or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bariydu Almawoti","text_ar":"بَرِيدُ المَوْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the messenger of death"},{"kind":"text","text":"], or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAbu Almawoti","text_ar":"بَابُ المَوْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the gate of death"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hum~apN","text_ar":"حُمَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (K, TA:) pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hum~ayaAtN","text_ar":"حُمَّيَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["Lh","L","K","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n9225","headword_ar":"حِمًى","root":"HmY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prohibited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"interdicted;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HimaA='N","text_ar":"حِمَا=ءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HimoyapN","text_ar":"حِمْيَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not to be approached:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) [and, as an epithet in which the quality of a subst. is predominant,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place of herbage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pasture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Mgh, Msb, * TA, and Ham p. 539,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and of water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham ibid.,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prohibited to the people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the public,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Lth, Mgh, and Ham ubi suprà,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that they may not pasture their beasts in it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor approach it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor venture upon it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) it was a custom of the noble among the Arabs, in the Time of Ignorance, when he alighted in a district [that pleased him], among his kinsfolk, to incite a dog to bark, and to prohibit for his own special friends or dependents the space throughout which the bark of the dog was heard, so that none else should pasture his beasts there; while he shared with the people in the other places of pasture, around it: but the Prophet forbade this: (Esh-Sháfi'ee, TA:) he said, “ There shall be no"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HmY","text_ar":"حمى"},{"kind":"text","text":"except for God and for his Apostle; ” (Esh-Sháfi'ee, S, Mgh, TA;) meaning, except for the horses employed in war against the unbelievers and for the camels taken for the poor-rate: (Esh-Sháfi'ee, Mgh, TA:) afterwards, the term was applied in a general sense: (Esh-Sháfi'ee, TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHomaA='N","text_ar":"اَحْمَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S"},{"kind":"page_break","n":652},{"kind":"text","text":"and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hjr","text_ar":"حجر"},{"kind":"text","text":") and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHomiyapN","text_ar":"اَحْمِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ham p. 496:) and the dual is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HimayaAni","text_ar":"حِمَيَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HimawaAni","text_ar":"حِمَوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (ISk, S, Msb, TA;) the latter irreg., (TA,) heard by Ks, but be preferred the former. (S.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA $aYo'N","text_ar":"هٰذَا شَىْءٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HimFY","text_ar":"حِمًى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a thing prohibited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"interdicted; not to be approached."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalaA^N HimFY","text_ar":"كَلَاٌ حِمًى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Herbage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pasture, that is prohibited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"interdicted."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HimaA='N","text_ar":"حِمَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","Lth","Mgh","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n9228","headword_ar":"حَمِىٌّ","root":"HmY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A sick man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prohibited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"interdicted, from what would injure him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of food and drink."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Protected, defended,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guarded"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Mgh, K, TA) from evil, &c. (TA.) 'Ásim Ibn-Thábit El Ansáree was called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamiY~u","text_ar":"حَمِىُّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~abori","text_ar":"الدَّبْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The protected by hornets,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the swarm of bees"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, Mgh,) because his corpse was protected from his enemies by large hornets, (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dbr","text_ar":"دبر"},{"kind":"text","text":",) or by a swarm of bees. (Mgh.)       -A2-  One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who will not bear, endure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tolerate, wrongful treatment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamiY~u AlA^anofi","text_ar":"حَمِىُّ الاَنْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who refuses to submit to wrongful treatment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anofN","text_ar":"اَنْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":["IAar","K","S","Mgh"]}]}}